  "content": "<p data-pid=\"xuQgxXkw\">为了表示学习和决策的价值，大脑必须对以下信息进行编码：（1）<b>动机相关性</b>和（2）<b>情感价值</b>。众所周知，在表示学习、决策和其他方面的估值上，伏隔核（NAcc）和中脑腹侧被盖区（VTA）起着关键作用。[…] 正如以往研究所预测的那样，无论是在自我导向还是慈善导向的实验中，NAcc 和 VTA 的激活在预期收益时增加，同时在预期损失时也增加。</p><hr/><p data-pid=\"6w0GjWKs\">引用的摘录来自以下<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//supermemo.guru/wiki/References\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">参考资料</a>：</p><p data-pid=\"Kz_VLO6R\">标题： <b>Activation in the VTA and nucleus accumbens increases in anticipation of both gains and losses</b></p><p data-pid=\"ZKacFaX7\">日期：2009 年</p><p data-pid=\"EVzBds9F\">反向链接：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//supermemo.guru/wiki/Pleasure_of_learning\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">学习的乐趣</a><sup data-text=\"学习的乐趣\" data-url=\"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/602150910\" data-draft-node=\"inline\" data-draft-type=\"reference\" data-numero=\"1\">[1]</sup></p><p data-pid=\"yPX96HQC\">链接：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=http%3A//journal.frontiersin.org/article/10.3389/neuro.08.021.2009/full\" class=\" external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><span class=\"invisible\">http://</span><span class=\"visible\">journal.frontiersin.org</span><span class=\"invisible\">/article/10.3389/neuro.08.021.2009/full</span><span class=\"ellipsis\"></span></a></p><p class=\"ztext-empty-paragraph\"><br/></p><blockquote data-pid=\"XvuZ_Xha\"><a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=http%3A//paratranz.cn/projects/3131\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Thoughts Memo</a> 汉化组译制<br/>感谢主要译者 GPT-4、校对 JarrettYe<br/>原文：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//supermemo.guru/wiki/Brain_centers_involved_in_valuation_of_anticipated_outcomes%3A_nucleus_accumbens_and_VTA\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Brain centers involved in valuation of anticipated outcomes: nucleus accumbens and VTA - supermemo.guru</a><br/>本<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//supermemo.guru/wiki/References\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">参考资料</a>用于支持<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//supermemo.guru/wiki/Piotr_Wozniak\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">彼得·沃兹尼亚克</a><sup data-text=\"彼得 · 沃兹尼亚克\" data-url=\"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/303204832\" data-draft-node=\"inline\" data-draft-type=\"reference\" data-numero=\"2\">[2]</sup>博士关于记忆、学习、创造力和问题解决系列文章中的一部分观点。</blockquote>",
